<subSubSection id="5B10915EAC28EACADF8A58007BDB4FAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C6385292ED3B39AE693B8AE2C76D423A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F633218B8A3EE3C8D1E7054A7095D92" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
An erect species with white, sericeous to tomentose vegetative parts and very small leaves. Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="155C1B310F83535A75CF08CD4413DD90" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durangensis">
<emphasis id="43E530D8D7E0C53D60C517B279438915" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea durangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing in the obtuse sepals. Specimens from Aguascalientes are somewhat intermediate with 
<taxonomicName id="511658C6FBEB95F854705100D8EBAFB6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="durangensis">
<emphasis id="1F76A65FB5E4B3A4336D6183FB5199FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea durangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
